com.netflix.msl.userauth
Class UserAuthenticationData

java.lang.Object
  com.netflix.msl.userauth.UserAuthenticationData
Direct Known Subclasses:
EmailPasswordAuthenticationData
public abstract class UserAuthenticationData
extends Object

The user authentication data provides proof of user identity.

Specific user authentication mechanisms should define their own user authentication data types.

User authentication data is represented as userauthdata = { "#mandatory" : [ "scheme"., "authdata" ], "scheme" : "string", "authdata" : object } where

  • scheme is the user authentication scheme
  • authdata is the scheme-specific authentication data

create

public static UserAuthenticationData create(MslContext ctx,
                                            MasterToken masterToken,
                                            JSONObject userAuthJO)
                                     throws MslUserAuthException,
                                            MslEncodingException,
                                            MslCryptoException

Construct a new user authentication data instance of the correct type from the provided JSON object.

A master token may be required for certain user authentication schemes.

Parameters:
ctx - MSL context.
masterToken - the master token associated with the user authentication data. May be null.
userAuthJO - the JSON object.
Returns:
the user authentication data concrete instance.
Throws:
MslEncodingException - if there is an error parsing the JSON.
MslUserAuthException - if there is an error instantiating the user authentication data.
MslCryptoException - if there is an error with the entity authentication data cryptography.
